{"parse": {"title": "Miriam Night", "pageid": 14562, "text": {"*": "<div class=\"mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><div class=\"eraicon filtericon\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Cyberpunk_2077\" title=\"Cyberpunk 2077\"><img alt=\"2077Icon\" src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/cyberpunk/images/7/77/2077Icon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/80?cb=20180612180205\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"80\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element\" data-image-name=\"2077Icon.png\" data-image-key=\"2077Icon.png\" data-relevant=\"1\" /></a></span></div>\n<p>\n<aside role=\"region\" class=\"portable-infobox pi-background pi-border-color pi-theme-wikia pi-layout-default\">\n<h2 class=\"pi-item pi-item-spacing pi-title pi-secondary-background\" data-source=\"title\">Miriam Night</h2>\n<section class=\"pi-item pi-group pi-border-color\">\n\t<h2 class=\"pi-item pi-header pi-secondary-font pi-item-spacing pi-secondary-background\">Biographical Information</h2>\n\n<div class=\"pi-item pi-data pi-item-spacing pi-border-color\" data-source=\"status\">\n\t\n\t\t<h3 class=\"pi-data-label pi-secondary-font\">Status</h3>\n\t\n\t<div class=\"pi-data-value pi-font\">Unknown</div>\n</div>\n\n</section>\n<section class=\"pi-item pi-group pi-border-color\">\n\t<h2 class=\"pi-item pi-header pi-secondary-font pi-item-spacing pi-secondary-background\">Physical Information</h2>\n\n<div class=\"pi-item pi-data pi-item-spacing pi-border-color\" data-source=\"gender\">\n\t\n\t\t<h3 class=\"pi-data-label pi-secondary-font\">Gender</h3>\n\t\n\t<div class=\"pi-data-value pi-font\">Female</div>\n</div>\n\n</section>\n<section class=\"pi-item pi-group pi-border-color\">\n\t<h2 class=\"pi-item pi-header pi-secondary-font pi-item-spacing pi-secondary-background\">Family</h2>\n\n<div class=\"pi-item pi-data pi-item-spacing pi-border-color\" data-source=\"partner\">\n\t\n\t\t<h3 class=\"pi-data-label pi-secondary-font\">Partner(s)</h3>\n\t\n\t<div class=\"pi-data-value pi-font\"><a href=\"/wiki/Richard_Night\" title=\"Richard Night\">Richard Night</a></div>\n</div>\n\n</section>\n<section class=\"pi-item pi-group pi-border-color\">\n\t<h2 class=\"pi-item pi-header pi-secondary-font pi-item-spacing pi-secondary-background\">Faction Information</h2>\n\n<div class=\"pi-item pi-data pi-item-spacing pi-border-color\" data-source=\"affiliation\">\n\t\n\t\t<h3 class=\"pi-data-label pi-secondary-font\">Affiliation</h3>\n\t\n\t<div class=\"pi-data-value pi-font\"><a href=\"/wiki/Night_Corp\" title=\"Night Corp\">Night Corp</a></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"pi-item pi-data pi-item-spacing pi-border-color\" data-source=\"role\">\n\t\n\t\t<h3 class=\"pi-data-label pi-secondary-font\">Role</h3>\n\t\n\t<div class=\"pi-data-value pi-font\"><a href=\"/wiki/Corporate\" title=\"Corporate\">Corporate</a></div>\n</div>\n\n</section>\n<section class=\"pi-item pi-group pi-border-color pi-collapse pi-collapse-closed\">\n\t<h2 class=\"pi-item pi-header pi-secondary-font pi-item-spacing pi-secondary-background\">Appearances</h2>\n\n<div class=\"pi-item pi-data pi-item-spacing pi-border-color\" data-source=\"appears_games\">\n\t\n\t\t<h3 class=\"pi-data-label pi-secondary-font\">Game(s)</h3>\n\t\n\t<div class=\"pi-data-value pi-font\"><i><a href=\"/wiki/Cyberpunk_2077\" title=\"Cyberpunk 2077\">Cyberpunk 2077</a></i></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"pi-item pi-data pi-item-spacing pi-border-color\" data-source=\"appears_books\">\n\t\n\t\t<h3 class=\"pi-data-label pi-secondary-font\">Literature</h3>\n\t\n\t<div class=\"pi-data-value pi-font\"><i><a href=\"/wiki/The_World_of_Cyberpunk_2077\" title=\"The World of Cyberpunk 2077\">The World of Cyberpunk 2077</a></i></div>\n</div>\n\n</section>\n</aside>\n\n<b>Miriam Night</b> was the founder of the Night Foundation, the CEO of <a href=\"/wiki/Night_Corp\" title=\"Night Corp\">Night Corp</a>, and the widow of <a href=\"/wiki/Night_City\" title=\"Night City\">Night City</a>'s founder, <a href=\"/wiki/Richard_Night\" title=\"Richard Night\">Richard Night</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">Biography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a title=\"Sign in to edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" data-tracking-label=\"log-in-edit-section\" data-action=\"edit-section\" href=\"https://auth.fandom.com/signin?redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fcyberpunk.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FMiriam_Night%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D1&amp;uselang=en\" data-testid=\"log-in-edit-section\"><svg class=\"wds-icon wds-icon-tiny\"><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-pencil-tiny\"></use></svg></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Before the construction of <a href=\"/wiki/Coronado_City\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coronado City\">Coronado City</a>, now known as Night City, in the <a href=\"/wiki/Timeline#1990s\" title=\"Timeline\">1990s</a>, Miriam met and married an ambitious entrepreneur and businessman by the name of <a href=\"/wiki/Richard_Night\" title=\"Richard Night\">Richard Night</a>. She was at his side while her husband built the city of his dreams. In 1998 Richard was assassinated, leaving her all his money and possessions, including Richard's own corporation, Night International.\n</p><p>A year later in 1999, Miriam restructured her husband's company and founded Night's Foundation, with the primary goal to protect and promote her husband's vision of the perfect city. For the next years, Miriam led the foundation onward, until the infamous <a href=\"/wiki/Mob_War\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mob War\">Mob War</a> occurred. She attempted to gain the support of the MegaCorps to end the reign of crime in the city, but to no avail. After the conflict, Miriam allegedly realized that to have any power in the city, you have to play by the rules of big businesses to get ahead. And so Night's Foundation was restructured, returning to its corporate roots, and renamed <a href=\"/wiki/Night_Corp\" title=\"Night Corp\">Night Corp</a>, with Miriam becoming its CEO.\n</p><p>Since then, Night Corp remained a constant presence in Night City, expanding its field of activity, but avoiding power struggles with other major corporations. Although Miriam stepped down from the role of CEO long before, her legacy and ideals were upheld by her successors.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Web_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Web-1\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>1<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-World_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-World-2\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>2<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a title=\"Sign in to edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" data-tracking-label=\"log-in-edit-section\" data-action=\"edit-section\" href=\"https://auth.fandom.com/signin?redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fcyberpunk.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FMiriam_Night%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D2&amp;uselang=en\" data-testid=\"log-in-edit-section\"><svg class=\"wds-icon wds-icon-tiny\"><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-pencil-tiny\"></use></svg></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"width:auto; min-height:6em; max-height:12em; height:auto; background-color:;; overflow:auto; margin-bottom:3px; padding: 0.2em 0.5em 0em 0.5em; border:1px solid var(--cyberpunkwiki-accent-color);\">\n<div class=\"references-small\"><div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Web-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Web_1-0\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Night City website in <i><a href=\"/wiki/Cyberpunk_2077\" title=\"Cyberpunk 2077\">Cyberpunk 2077</a></i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-World-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-World_2-0\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">BATYLDA, M. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_World_of_Cyberpunk_2077\" title=\"The World of Cyberpunk 2077\">The World of Cyberpunk 2077</a></i>. 1st ed. Milwaukie, OR, <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.darkhorse.com/\">Dark Horse Books</a>, 2020. (p.138)</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div></div>\n</div>"}, "images": ["2077Icon.png"]}}